This paper deals with predicting human behavior in the context of human-in-the-loop experimentation, which involves both human-computer interaction (HCI) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The paper also discusses multi-fidelity methods, which involve combining data from different sources, and machine learning techniques, which involve building models to predict behavior. Therefore, the paper could also belong to categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
